# Allowlist, not denylist: ignore the whole context, then re-include only what the
# build actually needs. A denylist is fragile — any new or churning root file (logs,
# mutants.out, editor temp) silently enters `COPY . .`, changes the context hash, and
# busts the builder layer cache, forcing a full recompile. Ignoring everything by
# default means only the paths below can ever affect the build.
*

# Rust workspace
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!.cargo
!rust-toolchain.toml
!crates

# config/ is baked into runner images (COPY config/*.toml); models/ is baked into the
# binaries at build time (face-detection/text-detection build.rs read ../../models).
!config
!models
